       The Lord is  speaking to Joshua and says, 'Fear them not: for I have
       delivered them into thine hand: there  shall not a man of them stand
       before thee.'

       Joshua was concerned because he was surrounded by the  enemy  and if
       darkness fell they  would  be  overpowered  by a superior force.  So
       Joshua asked the Lord to make the sun stand still!

       That's right---'the sun  stood  still,  and  the  moon  stayed...and
       hasted not to go down about a whole day.'

       (Joshua 10:8, 12-13)  The  modern spacemen, said,  'Well  there's  a
       missing day alright.'  They  checked  the computers, going back into
       the time it was written and found  it  was  close to correct but not
       quite close enough.  The elapsed time that was missing  in  Joshua's
       time was computed  at  23 hours and 20 minutes---not a whole day, 24
       hours.  They reread the scripture  and  and  there  it  was---'about
       (approximately) a whole day.'"

       "These little words in the Bible are extremely important.  Yet  they
       were still in trouble because if you cannot account for 40 minutes ,
       you will be  in  trouble  in the future due to multiplication of the
       error many times over in the intervening years of mega-orbits."

       "This religious fellow once again  came  to  the  rescue and said he
       remembered somewhere in  the  Bible  where  it  said  the  sun  went
       BACKWARDS!  He was told he was out of his mind.

       Still they took  out  the  'Book'  once  more and found in II Kings:
       Hezekiah, on his death bed, was visited  by  the prophet Isaiah, who
       told him that he was not going to die.  Hezekiah  asked  for  a sign
       from heaven as proof.  Isaiah said, 'Do you want the sun to go ahead
       ten degrees?'

       Hezekiah said, 'It  is nothing for the sun to go forward 10 degrees,
       But let the shadow return backward 10 degrees.' (II Kings 20:9-11)

       Isaiah spoke to the Lord and the Lord brought the shadow 10 degrees
       backward!  This according to scripture.   Ten  degrees is exactly 40
       minutes!"

       "Twenty-three hours and twenty minutes in Joshua, plus 40 minutes in
       II kings makes 24 hours.  Twenty-four hours are missing  in  elapsed
       time!  The Space  travelers  had to log in the logbook that this was
       the missing day in the universe!"

       "Isn't that amazing?"

       ( The above was also printed in a  newspaper  in  Spencer,  Indiana,
       October, 1970)
